Metadata: Coho Salmon: Life in the Watershed (revision)
The Oregon Department of Environmental Quality
Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife
This publication is a minor revision of ORESU-G-97-003 and from the Oregon Coastal Watershed Enhancement Project.

This fact sheet fills a need expressed by many involved with coho restoration for a summary that describes the relationship between the life history of the fish and the coastal habitats they occupy. The fact sheet is appropriate for landowners and others who can make a difference with coho, as well as for outreach staff, including extension agents, field staff, and watershed volunteers.
